d138481137b60c01d", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/da1e3c9635900eccd42262dd138481137b60c01d", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/da1e3c9635900eccd42262dd138481137b60c01d"}, {"sha": "c7d6dc49638bff3a0e1d1543f76afe1e697bd55c", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/c7d6dc49638bff3a0e1d1543f76afe1e697bd55c", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/c7d6dc49638bff3a0e1d1543f76afe1e697bd55c"}], "stats": {"total": 22, "additions": 22, "deletions": 0}, "files": [{"sha": "717ce4e5c5abe3c8a283b54774262811c829c040", "filename": "Processes.md", "status": "added", "additions": 22, "deletions": 0, "changes": 22, "blob_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/a2264cb5497e7a35c781ec726954cde5dfd76efc/Processes.md", "raw_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/raw/a2264cb5497e7a35c781ec726954cde5dfd76efc/Processes.md", "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/contents/Processes.md?ref=a2264cb5497e7a35c781ec726954cde5dfd76efc", "patch": "@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@\n+This document outlines processes regarding management of rustfmt.\n+\n+# Stabilising an Option\n+\n+In this Section, we describe how to stabilise an option of the rustfmt's configration.\n+\n+## Conditions\n+\n+- The design and implementation of the option are sound and clean.\n+- The option is well tested, both in unit tests and, optimally, in real usage.\n+- There is no open bug about the option that prevents its use.\n+\n+## Steps\n+\n+Open a pull request that closes the tracking issue. The tracking issue is listed beside the option in `Configurations.md`.\n+\n+- Update the `Config` enum marking the option as stable.\n+- Update the the `Configuration.md` file marking the option as stable.\n+\n+## After the stabilisation\n+\n+The option should remain backward-compatible with previous parameters of the option. For instance, if the option is an enum `enum Foo { Alice, Bob }` and the variant `Foo::Bob` is removed/renamed, existing use of the `Foo::Bob` variant should map to the new logic. Breaking changes can be applied under the condition they are version-gated."}]}